# Cursor AI Rules for DynamicCareerCanvas

# Read full documentation in CURSOR.md and AGENTS.md

## Project Type
Jekyll static site generator for professional portfolio

## Tech Stack
- Jekyll 4.x
- Liquid templating
- YAML data files
- SCSS styling
- Vanilla JavaScript (no frameworks)
- GitHub Pages hosting

## Core Rules

### DO
- Follow existing code patterns
- Keep it simple and readable
- Use YAML files in _data/ for content
- Use CSS variables for theming
- Make everything mobile responsive
- Add alt text to all images
- Test with: bundle exec jekyll build
- Include AI attribution in commits

### DON'T
- Add React, Vue, jQuery, or other frameworks
- Use inline styles
- Hardcode content in templates
- Skip mobile testing
- Remove accessibility features
- Commit without building first
- Add API keys or secrets

## File Structure

Content (edit often):
- _data/experience.yml
- _data/projects.yml
- _data/skills.yml
- _data/publications.yml

Templates:
- _includes/components/ (reusable UI)
- _layouts/ (page layouts)

Styles:
- _sass/base/ (variables, base styles)
- _sass/components/ (component styles)
- _sass/layout/ (layout styles)

## Code Style

### YAML
company: "Company Name"
title: "Job Title"
start_date: "YYYY-MM"
description: |
  Multi-line text

### HTML/Liquid
<!-- Comment explaining component -->
<div class="component-name">
  {{ include.data.title }}
</div>

### SCSS
.component-name {
  padding: var(--spacing-md);

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    padding: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
}

### JavaScript
const init = () => {
  // Modern ES6+, no jQuery
};
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', init);

## Testing
Always run before committing:
bundle exec jekyll build

For live preview:
bundle exec jekyll serve --livereload

